cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.FL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is likely because the paper presents logical characterizations of the relaxed notions of simulation and bisimulation on Probabilistic Automata. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is likely because the paper deals with probabilistic models and distances between states, which are relevant to AI applications such as decision making and reinforcement learning. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is likely because the paper discusses process algebra operators and their relationship with the defined distances. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is likely because the paper presents an algorithm for computing the relations in PTIME and compares the defined distances to others previously defined. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is likely because the paper deals with Probabilistic Automata and their simulation and bisimulation relations.
